description:
Follow our 'Pass The Aux' playlist for more tunes like this: win.gs/aux

Lil Herb, the MC sensation from East Side, Chicago and L.A.’s Earl Sweatshirt trade extra-gritty verses over this laid-back, sample-fueled banger, produced by Odd Future’s man of mystery himself. The two collaborated to write and record the song ahead of Red Bull Sound Select’s 4 Days in Austin during SXSW.

Support Lil Herb on his way to rap supremacy via Red Bull Sound Select: 

https://www.redbullsoundselect.com/artists/lilherb

The track is 4/20 of the Red Bull 20 Before 15 series – 20 days, 20 exclusive tracks to take you 

into 2015. For more tracks and free download head to: redbull.com/20before15

description:
Gray has been making waves at Born On Road HQ since our 1st slightly bizarre meeting with him in a field in Winchester at a popular music festival in 2018. Though his roots run a lot deeper. He cut his teeth though the free party scene in his hometown of London proving he has the minerals whist effortlessly mixing between styles.

Since moving to Bristol he has fully submerged himself into the circuit growing ever popular amongst ravers who have taken to joining in with the infectious vocals of his newly acclaimed anthem ‘Rubadub’, just one of the tunes off this heavyweight EP that has been doing major damage over the summer and is already turning the heads of some of the big players in the scene and it’s sub genres!

Gray has also enrolled the talents of two veterans of the scene, The Ragga Twins drop the lead line on Blood, a hard hitting bass heavy tune.

This EP is rammed packed full of goodness and comes with our certified Born On Road dance floor seal of approval, we are super hyped to welcome Gray as a member of our ever expanding family and we all look forward to working with him more in the future. But for now we’ll let the music do the talking…



Gray:

Soundcloud - https://soundcloud.com/gray_music
Facebook - https://www.facebook.com/graydrumandbass/
Instagram - https://www.instagram.com/graydnb/

description: Main boy from the Parallel Collective - Killa introduces us to the Parallel Mix Series. The New Plymouth lad has been ripping up the scene of late, headlining 'Seaside Sounds' at Butlers Reef (The Good Feels) and Parallel's packed takeover at 55. March was a huge month as he opened for both AC13 and Crossy (Born on Road), now Killa is quickly earning a name for his tasty selection.

description:
CXT004 presents the second of the label’s collaborative EPs where two producers present a solo track each alongside collaborating on two more tracks. 

Partners in crime Ebb & Texture by way of New Zealand are at the helm of CXT004. With a heavyweight solo track each - longtime Sicaria Sound set staple ‘5 Skin’ by Ebb alongside Texture’s formidable ‘No Mercy’ - the flip of the record then introduces two fierce collaborative efforts via low-end driven, lively breaks.

C1: Ebb - 5 Skin
C2: Texture - No Mercy
X1: Ebb x Texture - Enmesh
X2: Ebb x Texture - Cloudburst

Digital & Vinyl Pre-Order: linktr.ee/cutcrxss

Digital Artwork by Sicaria Sound
Digital Mastering by Liam McLean
Vinyl Mastering by Ten Eight Seven

Ebb - @ebb-nz
Texture - @texture_wav

The remastered title track from Eminem's debut album is now available digitally for the first time ever. Click here to stream or download it now: https://infinite.lnk.to/eminem 
When 'Infinite' was originally released in November of 1996, it sold out of all 500 pressed copies and the album still is not commercially available today. In addition, a 10-minute documentary short, 'Partners In Rhyme,' is also available now and features never-before-seen footage of Marshall Mathers in his early years when he was doing open mic nights in Detroit and recording at the Bass Brothers studio. Watch it here: http://smarturl.it/eminem_doc

→ http://bristolmixsessions.com

Watch these sets: https://youtu.be/QXJL3kJBlSU
_________________________

About this recording:

I am proud to present you Episode 51 of the Bristol Mix Sessions Livestream series. 

This time, I'm taking you back to 9th July 2021 in Bristol, U.K. with myself, Etherwood & Steve LP (BMS Resident) on the decks!

Clubs were open at the time but under seated restrictions. The Bristol Mix Sessions team & I curated seated events at Basement 45 when we could, bringing a host of talent (from Etherwood, Walk:r, In:Most, Something Something, Lilac, Shadows, Missledz & more) to hungry DnB fans. 

Now clubs are fully open in Bristol, the team & I are stepping up to provide you with the best DnB events we can. We've already booked artists such as Whiney, Telomic, Averse, Grey Code, Spectral, DJ Dazee, Natty Lou, Subtle Element, Lurch, Lally, Kyrist, PRSPKTV, Kublai, Note... + we've got shows planned in November & December. 

Keep up-to-date with our event schedule here: https://hdfst.uk/bristol-mix-sessions

Big thank you to Liv and Steve who work so hard to support the Bristol Mix Sessions. Thank you to Etherwood for coming down and playing a beautiful set and, finally, thank you to anyone who's bought tickets to one of our events - thank you for keeping Bristol's DnB scene alive and vibrant.

description: A few days ago one of our favourite people Vish (shout outs to DJ Vee) came around to see us and a party ensued. It was late, it was messy, it was (best believe) SUPER fun… and I DJed. Vee asked “can you record it?”, I said “no promises” and these are the results. There’s some reassuringly dodgy mixing and the occasional head-scratching transition (it’s a house party right?!) but overall it’s a really good time. The thing I like about it is it’s nothing like my club sets and feels a bit loosey goosey... In a good way. Happy new year humans.X

description: Part 2 of the live recording of one of my favourite Body Electric parties ever at Club 121. My guest Cian is a straight up legend in Aotearoa- the Body Electric dancers found out why that night! The atmosphere was absolutely electric; it was one of those nights where everything came together magically... a packed house full of openminded dancers and this kind of indefinable euphoria in the air- I can't quite describe it!

description:
It's with great pleasure we release mix number 2 for 2013, and Christopher Tubbs' tenth in the series.

If you haven't been in person to the Heads Down Sessions at Caravan, it's 6 hours of Balearica, disco, leftfield soul and a plethora of the weird and wonderful played to a gastrosonic crowd fuelled by some of the best tapas style cuisine and cocktails in London.

The next Caravan session is tomorrow, Saturday June the 17th at 6pm.

http://www.headsdown.org
